Global Funds Buy Net 48.7 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-06-27T03:32:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-27/global-funds-buy-net-48-7-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 48.7
billion rupees ($1.1 billion) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
June 24, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 2.6 percent to 987.4 billion rupees, or 33.8
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds bought a net 8.9 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on June 24, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
